msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:54
msgid "Shuriken now competes head-to-head with traditional post-rating plugins — but without forcing you to create a separate rating for every post. Place one rating (or grouped rating) in your single post template, flip the \"Per-post voting\" toggle, and every post on your site immediately gets its own independent vote tallies."
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:57
msgid "Zero-Config Per-Post Ratings"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:58
msgid "Add a rating block to your Single Post template, enable Per-post voting — done. Every post gets its own scores without creating hundreds of individual ratings."
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:61
msgid "One Template, Many Posts"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:62
msgid "The rating entity is defined once. Votes are scoped to each post via context_id / context_type columns on the votes table. Global aggregates remain intact for standalone use."
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:65
msgid "Grouped Ratings Too"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:66
msgid "The grouped rating block supports the same toggle. One parent + sub-rating configuration serves all posts — add or remove sub-ratings once and every post reflects the change instantly."
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:69
msgid "REST Compatible"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:70
msgid "The /ratings/stats endpoint accepts optional context_id and context_type parameters, returning per-post stats for any custom frontend or headless WordPress setup."
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:73
msgid "Extensible Context Types"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/settings-about.php:74
msgid "Supports post, page, and product out of the box. Add any custom post type via the shuriken_allowed_context_types filter."
